a:3:{s:11:"notes_total";i:4;s:11:"notes_ctree";a:4:{i:0;a:32:{s:2:"id";i:57;s:5:"title";s:95:"Email sending now includes a preview step across campaigns, sequences, and workflows in Folk";s:4:"href";s:94:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/all/email-sending-now-includes-a-preview-step-across-campaigns-seque/";s:13:"href-original";s:94:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/all/email-sending-now-includes-a-preview-step-across-campaigns-seque/";s:4:"time";a:2:{i:0;i:1769864640;i:1;a:2:{s:6:"offset";i:18000;s:6:"is_dst";b:0;}}s:13:"last-modified";a:2:{i:0;i:1769581126;i:1;a:2:{s:6:"offset";i:18000;s:6:"is_dst";b:0;}}s:4:"text";s:679:"<p>A preview feature is now available across three sending contexts: email campaigns, sequences, and workflows.</p>
<h3>What it does</h3>
<p>The preview is intended to reduce common last-mile mistakes before sending, such as:</p>
<ul>
<li>typos and formatting issues</li>
<li>personalization tokens not rendering correctly (e. g., a placeholder showing instead of a name)</li>
<li>missing file attachments</li>
</ul>
<h3>Where it’s available</h3>
<ul>
<li>Email campaigns</li>
<li>Sequences</li>
<li>Workflows</li>
</ul>
<p>Learn more here: <a href="https://www.folk.app/changelog/preview-before-sending">https://www.folk.app/changelog/preview-before-sending</a></p>
