ast-modified";a:2:{i:0;i:1769580824;i:1;a:2:{s:6:"offset";i:18000;s:6:"is_dst";b:0;}}s:4:"text";s:742:"<p>folk rolled out additional privacy settings aimed at reducing accidental exposure of sensitive communication inside the CRM.</p>
<h3>What’s new</h3>
<p>Auto-hide internal emails to limit visibility of internal threads.</p>
<p>Exclude sensitive contacts from views, including examples like investors, accountants, or personal email contacts.</p>
<h3>Why it matters</h3>
<p>For teams sharing the same workspace, visibility settings can affect compliance, confidentiality, and relationship management. These controls give users more granularity over what appears in shared CRM contexts.</p>
<p>Learn more: <a href="https://www.folk.app/changelog/privacy-on-your-terms">https://www.folk.app/changelog/privacy-on-your-terms</a></p>
