:13:"last-modified";a:2:{i:0;i:1769580608;i:1;a:2:{s:6:"offset";i:18000;s:6:"is_dst";b:0;}}s:4:"text";s:872:"<p>folk released Assistants, a feature designed to handle repetitive tasks that typically fall on sales and customer-facing teams.</p>
<h3>What’s included (as described)</h3>
<ul>
<li>Researching companies</li>
<li>Sending outreach emails</li>
<li>Identifying follow-ups</li>
<li>Recapping deals</li>
</ul>
<h3>Why it matters</h3>
<p>If the feature works as intended, it shifts some day-to-day CRM upkeep from manual effort to automation—especially around preparation, outreach, and next-step tracking.</p>
<h3>Product direction</h3>
<p>folk positions Assistants as part of building a CRM that behaves more proactively, surfacing and executing routine work rather than waiting for users to do it.</p>
<p>Learn more: <a href="https://www.folk.app/changelog/launching-assistants-library">https://www.folk.app/changelog/launching-assistants-library</a></p>
